################################################################################
# PURPOSE:
#   Unified H2 + H4 script for McKenzie nest-level spatial heterogeneity.
#
#   This script:
#     1) Tests H2 separately at each threshold using the same model structure:
#          - Detection model: AnyDetected ~ Nest_ID
#          - Richness model:  OTU_Richness ~ Nest_ID
#     2) Repeats that analysis across thresholds to explicitly evaluate H4
#        robustness.
#     3) Exports 1.0% threshold outputs for plotting and biological description.
#     4) Exports 1.0% OTU-level summaries to identify which taxa drive the pattern.
#
# INPUTS:
#   1) otu_table_collapsed_relative.csv
#   2) guild_table_collapsed.csv
#   3) metadata.csv
#
# THRESHOLDS:
#   - 0.0  -> interpreted as RA > 0
#   - 0.2  -> interpreted as RA >= 0.2
#   - 0.5  -> interpreted as RA >= 0.5
#   - 1.0  -> interpreted as RA >= 1.0
#   - 1.5  -> interpreted as RA >= 1.5
#
# FOCAL DATA SUBSET:
#   - Site: Mckenzie
#   - Nests: M1, M3, M6, M8, M9, M10
#
# FOCAL GUILDS:
#   - Truffle
#   - Epigeous_ECM
#
# MAIN OUTPUT GROUPS:
#   A) Combined sample- and nest-level summary tables across all thresholds
#   B) Per-threshold model outputs for detection and richness
#   C) Combined robustness summary table across thresholds
#   D) Dedicated 1.0% plotting tables
#   E) Dedicated 1.0% OTU-level interpretation tables
#
# NOTES:
#   - Relative abundance values are percentages summing to ~100 per sample.
#   - No pipes are used here to avoid %>% issues in the local session.
################################################################################

